1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. Bxc4 c5 6. O-O Nc6 { The main moves 7.Nc3 and 7.Qe2 will be analyzed in the upcoming lessons. } 7. dxc5 { It is better for White to include the moves 7.a3 a6 and only then capture on c5. This will be analyzed in the next lesson. } 7... Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Bxc5 { The difference without the inclusion of a3 and a6 is that now, Black can simply continue with b6 and Bb7, with a fine position. } 9. a3 ( 9. b3 O-O 10. Bb2 Be7 ( 10... b6 { Black can also choose to start with this move. } ) 11. Nbd2 b6 12. a3 Bb7 $11 { 1/2-1/2 (42) Radjabov,T (2765) -Dominguez Perez,L (2758) chess24.com INT 2021 } ) ( 9. Nc3 O-O { Transposes to the previous lesson. } ) 9... O-O 10. b4 Be7 11. Bb2 b6 12. Nc3 Bb7 13. Nd2 ( 13. Be2 Rfd8 $11 { 1/2-1/2 (32) Bai,J (2618) -Xu,X (2573) Xinghua CHN 2020 } ) 13... Rfd8 14. Be2 Rac8 15. Nc4 Ne8 $11 { [%cal Gg8f8,Ge7f6] Black has a very solid position with no weaknesses. } *[Event "?"]
