{[#]} {Black to move} 10... Nd7 $1 {[%cal Gd7c5] An important move, intending to capture the c5-pawn with the knight and additionally, e4-e5 won't come with tempo in the future.} 11. Bf4 (11. Nc3 Nxc5 {Doesn't change much.}) (11. Rd1 Qc7 {This is also fine for Black.}) 11... Nxc5 12. Rd1 Bd7 13. Nc3 Qb6 $11 {Intending Rfd8 and Rac8 next. The position is pleasant for Black since the knight on c5 is untouchable because the pawn is already on a4, if it was on a3 however, it would have been a different story due to b2-b4. In addition, Black enjoys control over the b4 and a5-squares in this position.} *

